QUESTION 5
========================================

The following source file, matvec.c contains the implementation of the 
matvec.py introducted in class implemented in C using MPI and the BLAS
library routines for vector and matrix operations.


Execution
----------------------------------------

Before executing the implementation you must have the BLAS/LAPACK
libraries installed on your system, follow the instructions below.

1. To install the BLAS/LAPACK libraries on most Ubuntu based Linux
   systems simply install the following packages.

   sudo apt-get install build-essential liblapack* libblas*

2. After installing the BLAS/LAPACK libraries you can then
   build and execute the code using the following commands.

   make
   mpiexec -np 4 ./matvec.exe
